OPEN-CORE SAFETY PROPERTY

The server MIT entrypoints (files outside any ee/ directory under server/src/) are
build-strip-safe: they use lazy dynamic imports guarded by try/catch so that removing
the server/src/ee/ tree causes each feature to degrade to free / can()===false behaviour
rather than crashing. A fork that strips only server/src/ee/ obtains a fully functional
free server install.

The admin panel MIT files (files outside admin/src/ee/) are NOT build-strip-safe:
they statically import from admin/src/ee/ using ESM static imports that cannot be
guarded by try/catch. A fork that also wants a stripped admin panel must rebuild the
admin without the admin/src/ee/ import surface. The admin degrades to free at RUNTIME
via the free sentinel default in admin/src/ee/context/LicenseContext.ts (can() always
false, tier/state 'free'), so the panel renders free whenever the license fetch fails
or the provider is absent -- no crash, no over-grant, all gated controls show
locked/upsell UI.

This distinction is intentional and documented. The server build-strip guarantee applies
only to server/src/ entrypoints.

